name: integer_i32_negative_one
description: |
  This is -1, represented with every bit set in two's-complement i32. It
  is the divisor that makes i32 minimum division overflow and exposes
  arithmetic-versus-logical shifts, sign extension, and signed-to-unsigned
  conversion. The same bytes represent u32 maximum.
format: hex
decode-as: i32
pair:
  - with: ../u32/maximum.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i32"
  - "negative"
  - "division"
  - "sign-extension"
  - "conversion"
  - "two's-complement"
  - "all-bits-set"
---
ff ff ff ff # -1
